"Bat various are the ways to change the state Of plants, to bud, to graff, to inoculate. For, where the tender rinds of trees disclose Their shooting gems, a swelling knot there grows : Just in that space a narrow slit we make ; Then other buds from bearing trees we take ; Inserted thus, the wounded rind we close, In whose moist womb theâ€™ admitted infant grows, But, when the smoother bole from knots is free, We make a deep incision in the tree,"